OL,3,CNon-smoker status 'worked against' dad
OL,4,Cbefore lung cancer diagnosis
OL,6,FFocusing too much on smoking status
OL,7,Fwhen someone has lung cancer symptoms
OL,8,Fcould lead to people not getting
OL,9,Fdiagnosed as quickly as they should, a
OL,10,Fcharity has warned.
OL,12,FThe "smoker" and "non-smoker" labels
OL,13,Fgiven to those who complain of
OL,14,Fsymptoms has a "direct impact" on the
OL,15,Fspeed at which the illness is
OL,16,Fdetected, Roy Castle Lung Cancer
OL,17,FFoundation claims.
